  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse by making partial restitution. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, an extensive prison sentence would be disproportionate to the offense and the amount stolen. The outburst from the spectator is disregarded as it does not reflect the legal standards for sentencing. A period of six months is sufficient to address the punitive and rehabilitative needs of the case.",
  "verdict": 6
}
